wwpLeosVlanMIB.name: wwpLeosVlanMIB
wwpLeosVlanMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
wwpLeosVlanMIB.description: This MIB module defines the managed objects for the VLAN, specific for the WWP products.

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A Vlan ID represents a Broadcast Domain.

VlanTag.name: VlanTag
VlanTag.description: A 12-bit ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

wwpLeosMaxVlans.name: wwpLeosMaxVlans
wwpLeosMaxVlans.description: The maximum number of VLANs that this device supports.

wwpLeosMaxSupportedVlanTagId.name: wwpLeosMaxSupportedVlanTagId
wwpLeosMaxSupportedVlanTagId.description: The maximum value of VLAN Tag ID that this device supports.

wwpLeosNumVlans.name: wwpLeosNumVlans
wwpLeosNumVlans.description: The current number of VLANs that are configured in this device.

wwpLeosVlanTable.name: wwpLeosVlanTable
wwpLeosVlanTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the config parameters for the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanEntry
wwpLeosVlanEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosVlanTable.

wwpLeosVlanId.name: wwpLeosVlanId
wwpLeosVlanId.description: A unique identifier for the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanName.name: wwpLeosVlanName
wwpLeosVlanName.description: Name associated with this VLAN Entry.

wwpLeosVlanStatus.name: wwpLeosVlanStatus
wwpLeosVlanStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table, there should not be any port/tag associated with this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanMacLrnState.name: wwpLeosVlanMacLrnState
wwpLeosVlanMacLrnState.description: Setting this object will enable or disable MAC learning for the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanMacLrnOperState.name: wwpLeosVlanMacLrnOperState
wwpLeosVlanMacLrnOperState.description: Displays the operational status of MAC learning for the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanTranslationVlan.name: wwpLeosVlanTranslationVlan
wwpLeosVlanTranslationVlan.description: The translated VLAN for the given ingress VLAN specified by wwpLeosVlanId. Setting this MIB object to 0 will result in unsetting the translation VLAN for given ingress VLAN wwpLeosVlanId.

wwpLeosVlanEgressTpid.name: wwpLeosVlanEgressTpid
wwpLeosVlanEgressTpid.description: This object specifies the tpid used at egress for frames that egress a port on this vlan. This is used in conjunction with port egress tpid policy described in wwpLeosVplsVirtualCircuitEtherTypePolicy.

wwpLeosVlanTagMemberTable.name: wwpLeosVlanTagMemberTable
wwpLeosVlanTagMemberTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the configuration parameters for the members of the VLANs.

wwpLeosVlanTagMemberEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanTagMemberEntry
wwpLeosVlanTagMemberEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosVlanTagMemberTable.

wwpLeosVlanMemberPortId.name: wwpLeosVlanMemberPortId
wwpLeosVlanMemberPortId.description: The port ID to be associated with this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanMemberTagId.name: wwpLeosVlanMemberTagId
wwpLeosVlanMemberTagId.description: The VLAN Tag ID used by the port on this VLAN. If the switch is being used as a traditional Layer 2 device, then the value of wwpLeosVlanMemberTagId should be same as wwpLeosVlanMemberId.

wwpLeosVlanMemberStatus.name: wwpLeosVlanMemberStatus
wwpLeosVlanMemberStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitTable.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitTable
wwpLeosVlanCircuitTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the virtual circuit table.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitEntry
wwpLeosVlanCircuitEntry.description: The virtual circuit table entry indexed by virtual circuit index. To create an entry, use the SNMP multiple set operation because wwpLeosCircuitVlanId, wwpLeosCircuitName and wwpLeosCircuitType are mandatory while creating entry in the table.

wwpLeosCircuitIndex.name: wwpLeosCircuitIndex
wwpLeosCircuitIndex.description: This represents the virtual circuit index in the table.

wwpLeosCircuitVlanId.name: wwpLeosCircuitVlanId
wwpLeosCircuitVlanId.description: This represents the VLAN ID associated with virtual circuit index in the table.

wwpLeosCircuitType.name: wwpLeosCircuitType
wwpLeosCircuitType.description: This represents the type of virtual circuit eth or mpls.

wwpLeosCircuitName.name: wwpLeosCircuitName
wwpLeosCircuitName.description: This represents the name associated with the virtual circuit.

wwpLeosCircuitPriority.name: wwpLeosCircuitPriority
wwpLeosCircuitPriority.description: This represents the 802.1D priority associated with the virtual circuit.

wwpLeosCircuitDataTunnelState.name: wwpLeosCircuitDataTunnelState
wwpLeosCircuitDataTunnelState.description: This represents the data tunnel state associated with the virtual circuit. Setting to 'on' enables the tunnel for data frames. Setting to 'off' disables it.

wwpLeosCircuitCtrlProtocolTunnelState.name: wwpLeosCircuitCtrlProtocolTunnelState
wwpLeosCircuitCtrlProtocolTunnelState.description: This represents the control frame tunnel state associated with the virtual circuit. Setting to 'on' enables the tunnel for control frames. Setting to 'off' disables it.

wwpLeosCircuitNumEndPoints.name: wwpLeosCircuitNumEndPoints
wwpLeosCircuitNumEndPoints.description: This represents the number of end points associated with this entry.

wwpLeosCircuitStatus.name: wwpLeosCircuitStatus
wwpLeosCircuitStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry and by default will enable control frame and data frame tunnel . Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table for given VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitPortExclusiveTable.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitPortExclusiveTable
wwpLeosVlanCircuitPortExclusiveTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the layer 2 control frame tunnel status on a VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitPortExclusiveEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitPortExclusiveEntry
wwpLeosVlanCircuitPortExclusiveEntry.description: The layer 2 control frame protocol tunnel entry for the VLAN.

wwpLeosPortId.name: wwpLeosPortId
wwpLeosPortId.description: This specifies the port which is the end point for in this virtual circuit.

wwpLeosPortExclusiveStatus.name: wwpLeosPortExclusiveStatus
wwpLeosPortExclusiveStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will create the entry and designate the port as the end point of the virtual circuit. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table for the given virtual circuit.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitCtrlProtocolTable.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitCtrlProtocolTable
wwpLeosVlanCircuitCtrlProtocolTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the layer 2 control frame protocol status tunnel for a given VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitCtrlProtocolEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitCtrlProtocolEntry
wwpLeosVlanCircuitCtrlProtocolEntry.description: The layer 2 control frame protocol tunnel entry for the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2ProtocolNum.name: wwpLeosVlanl2ProtocolNum
wwpLeosVlanl2ProtocolNum.description: This object represent the list of protocols supported by the device.

wwpLeosVlanl2Type.name: wwpLeosVlanl2Type
wwpLeosVlanl2Type.description: Setting this object to 'discard' will cause wwpLeosProtocolNum frames arriving at the specified UNI to be discarded. Setting this to 'peer' will cause the wwpLeosProtocolNum frame to be processed by the provider network and cause the provider network to behave as a peer. Setting this to 'tunnel' will cause the wwpLeosProtocolNum frame to be tunneled.

wwpLeosVlanl2AllRxPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2AllRxPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2AllRxPkts.description: Specifies total number of packets ingressed on VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2AllTunneledPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2AllTunneledPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2AllTunneledPkts.description: Specifies the total number of packets tunneled on the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2AllPeerPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2AllPeerPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2AllPeerPkts.description: Specifies the total number of packets peered on the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2AllDiscardedPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2AllDiscardedPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2AllDiscardedPkts.description: Specifies the total number of discarded packets on the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2AllDecodedPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2AllDecodedPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2AllDecodedPkts.description: Specifies the total number of packets tunneled and then restored on the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2AllDecodedFailures.name: wwpLeosVlanl2AllDecodedFailures
wwpLeosVlanl2AllDecodedFailures.description: Specifies the total number of packets failed to 'untunnel' on the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2AllTunneledSubcriberPortPkt.name: wwpLeosVlanl2AllTunneledSubcriberPortPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2AllTunneledSubcriberPortPkt.description: Specifies the total number of tunneled packets received on the subscriber port on the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitProtocolStatsTable.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitProtocolStatsTable
wwpLeosVlanCircuitProtocolStatsTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the layer 2 control frame protocol statistics for a given VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanCircuitProtocolStatsEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanCircuitProtocolStatsEntry
wwpLeosVlanCircuitProtocolStatsEntry.description: The layer 2 control frame protocol statistics entry for the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanl2RxPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2RxPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2RxPkts.description: Specifies the number of packets ingressed matching the protocol.

wwpLeosVlanl2TunneledPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2TunneledPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2TunneledPkts.description: Specifies the number of packets tunneled.

wwpLeosVlanl2PeerPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2PeerPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2PeerPkts.description: Specifies the number of peered packets.

wwpLeosVlanl2DiscardedPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2DiscardedPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2DiscardedPkts.description: Specifies the number of discarded packets.

wwpLeosVlanl2DecodedPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2DecodedPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2DecodedPkts.description: Specifies the number of packets tunneled and then restored.

wwpLeosVlanl2DecodedFailures.name: wwpLeosVlanl2DecodedFailures
wwpLeosVlanl2DecodedFailures.description: Specifies the number of packets failed to 'untunnel'.

wwpLeosVlanl2TunneledSubcriberPortPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanl2TunneledSubcriberPortPkts
wwpLeosVlanl2TunneledSubcriberPortPkts.description: Specifies the number of tunneled packets received on the subscriber port.

wwpLeosVlanStatsTable.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsTable
wwpLeosVlanStatsTable.description: A list of VLAN statistics entries.

wwpLeosVlanStatsEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsEntry
wwpLeosVlanStatsEntry.description: An entry in the VLAN stats table.

wwpLeosVlanStatsVlanId.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsVlanId
wwpLeosVlanStatsVlanId.description: The VLAN ID for this statistics entry.

wwpLeosVlanStatsCreateTime.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsCreateTime
wwpLeosVlanStatsCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this control entry was last activated. This value can be used by the management station to ensure that the entry has not been deleted and recreated between polls.

wwpLeosVlanStatsUniOctets.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsUniOctets
wwpLeosVlanStatsUniOctets.description: The number of unicast bytes through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanStatsUniPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsUniPkts
wwpLeosVlanStatsUniPkts.description: The number of unicast packets through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanStatsNonUniOctets.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsNonUniOctets
wwpLeosVlanStatsNonUniOctets.description: The number of broadcast or multicast bytes through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanStatsNonUniPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsNonUniPkts
wwpLeosVlanStatsNonUniPkts.description: The number of broadcast or multicast packets through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanStatsStatus.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsStatus
wwpLeosVlanStatsStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will enable the collection of statistics on the specified VLAN, clear the initial statistics bucket and add the entry to the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will disable the collection of statistics and remove the entry from the table for given VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanStatsClear.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsClear
wwpLeosVlanStatsClear.description: Setting this object to True will reset the statistics of the given VLAN. Read on this object will always return False.

wwpLeosVlanStatsPortId.name: wwpLeosVlanStatsPortId
wwpLeosVlanStatsPortId.description: The port ID to be associated with this VLAN statistics entry. When a portId is specified, VLAN statistics gathering is restricted to the specified port. A port ID of zero means no port restriction. Support for this object is currently not implemented.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsTable.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsTable
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsTable.description: A list of VLAN statistics entries.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsEntry
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsEntry.description: An entry in the VLAN statistics table.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsVlanId.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsVlanId
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsVlanId.description: The VLAN ID for this statistics entry.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsCreateTime.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsCreateTime
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this control entry was last activated. This value can be used by the management station to ensure that the entry has not been deleted and recreated between polls.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsUniOctets.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsUniOctets
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsUniOctets.description: The number of unicast bytes through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsUniPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsUniPkts
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsUniPkts.description: The number of unicast packets through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsNonUniOctets.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsNonUniOctets
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsNonUniOctets.description: The number of broadcast or multicast bytes through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsNonUniPkts.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsNonUniPkts
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsNonUniPkts.description: The number of broadcast or multicast packets through this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsStatus.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsStatus
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createAndGo' will enable the collection of statistics on the specified VLAN, clear the initial statistics bucket and add the entry to the table. Setting this object to 'destroy' will disable the collection of statistics and remove the entry from the table for given VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsClear.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsClear
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsClear.description: Setting this object to True resets the statistics of the given VLAN. Read on this object will always return False.

wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsPortId.name: wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsPortId
wwpLeosVlanTotalStatsPortId.description: The port ID to be associated with this VLAN statistics entry. When a portId is specified, the VLAN statistics gathering is restricted to the specified port. A port ID of zero means no port restriction. Support for this object is currently not implemented.

wwpLeosVlanTranslationEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanTranslationEntry
wwpLeosVlanTranslationEntry.description: An entry in the VLAN translation table.

wwpLeosVlanTranslationPgId.name: wwpLeosVlanTranslationPgId
wwpLeosVlanTranslationPgId.description: Logical port interface for which the translation applies.

wwpLeosVlanTranslationStatus.name: wwpLeosVlanTranslationStatus
wwpLeosVlanTranslationStatus.description: Setting this object to CreateAndGo will create a VLAn tranlsation entry. Setting this object to destroy will delete a translation entry.

wwpLeosVlanEPRTable.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRTable
wwpLeosVlanEPRTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the egress port restriction parameters for the VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanEPREntry.name: wwpLeosVlanEPREntry
wwpLeosVlanEPREntry.description: The egress port restriction entry for a VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanEPRState.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRState
wwpLeosVlanEPRState.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will enable the egress port restriction on this VLAN. Setting this object to 'disable' will disable the egress port restriction on this VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpMemTable.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpMemTable
wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpMemTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the egress port restriction group for the VLAN members.

wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpMemEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpMemEntry
wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpMemEntry.description: The egress port restriction group entry for the VLAN members.

wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpName.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpName
wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpName.description: Setting this object will assign the specified group to the given port-tag-vlan combination.

wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAccessTable.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAccessTable
wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAccessTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the group access for the given VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAccessEntry.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAccessEntry
wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAccessEntry.description: Entry for the group access for the given VLAN.

wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAAccess.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAAccess
wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpAAccess.description: Setting this object will allow group A members for this VLAN to talk to specified group.

wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpBAccess.name: wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpBAccess
wwpLeosVlanEPRGrpBAccess.description: Setting this object will allow group B members for this VLAN to talk to specified group.
